#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:153
msgid "Agree on a release schedule"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:154
msgid ""
"A typical release schedule is one beta, two release candidates and a final "
"release.  It's best to discuss the timing on the mailing list first, in "
"order for people to get their commits in on time, get doc wiki edits merged, "
"etc. After a date is set, create a new maintenance/x.y.z branch, add new "
"empty release notes for the next version in the main branch and update the "
"Trac Milestones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:163
msgid "Make sure current branch builds a package correctly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:164
msgid ""
"The CI builds wheels when a PR header begins with ``REL``. Your last PR "
"before releasing should be so marked and all the tests should pass. You can "
"also do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:168
msgid ""
"git clean -fxdq\n"
"python setup.py bdist_wheel\n"
"python setup.py sdist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:172
msgid ""
"For details of the build process itself, it is best to read the Step-by-Step "
"Directions below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:175
msgid ""
"The following steps are repeated for the beta(s), release candidates(s) and "
"the final release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:180
msgid "Check deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:181
msgid ""
"Before :ref:`the release branch is made <branching>`, it should be checked "
"that all deprecated code that should be removed is actually removed, and all "
"new deprecations say in the docstring or deprecation warning what version "
"the code will be removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:187
msgid "Check the C API version number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:188
msgid "The C API version needs to be tracked in three places"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:190
msgid "numpy/core/setup_common.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:191
msgid "numpy/core/code_generators/cversions.txt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:192
msgid "numpy/core/include/numpy/numpyconfig.h"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:194
msgid "There are three steps to the process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:196
msgid ""
"If the API has changed, increment the C_API_VERSION in setup_common.py. The "
"API is unchanged only if any code compiled against the current API will be "
"backward compatible with the last released NumPy version. Any changes to C "
"structures or additions to the public interface will make the new API not "
"backward compatible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:202
msgid ""
"If the C_API_VERSION in the first step has changed, or if the hash of the "
"API has changed, the cversions.txt file needs to be updated. To check the "
"hash, run the script numpy/core/cversions.py and note the API hash that is "
"printed. If that hash does not match the last hash in numpy/core/"
"code_generators/cversions.txt the hash has changed. Using both the "
"appropriate C_API_VERSION and hash, add a new entry to cversions.txt. If the "
"API version was not changed, but the hash differs, you will need to comment "
"out the previous entry for that API version. For instance, in NumPy 1.9 "
"annotations were added, which changed the hash, but the API was the same as "
"in 1.8. The hash serves as a check for API changes, but it is not definitive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:214
msgid ""
"If steps 1 and 2 are done correctly, compiling the release should not give a "
"warning \"API mismatch detect at the beginning of the build\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:217
msgid ""
"The numpy/core/include/numpy/numpyconfig.h will need a new "
"NPY_X_Y_API_VERSION macro, where X and Y are the major and minor version "
"numbers of the release. The value given to that macro only needs to be "
"increased from the previous version if some of the functions or macros in "
"the include files were deprecated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:223
msgid ""
"The C ABI version number in numpy/core/setup_common.py should only be "
"updated for a major release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:228
msgid "Check the release notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:229
msgid ""
"Use `towncrier`_ to build the release note and commit the changes. This will "
"remove all the fragments from ``doc/release/upcoming_changes`` and add ``doc/"
"release/<version>-note.rst``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../HOWTO_RELEASE.rst:233
msgid ""
"towncrier build --version \"<version>\" git commit -m\"Create release note\""
msgstr ""

