#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:1
msgid ""
"This is a walkthrough of the NumPy 1.21.0 release on Linux, modified for "
"building with GitHub Actions and cibuildwheels and uploading to the "
"`anaconda.org staging repository for NumPy <https://anaconda.org/multibuild-"
"wheels-staging/numpy>`_. The commands can be copied into the command line, "
"but be sure to replace 1.21.0 by the correct version. This should be read "
"together with the :ref:`general release guide <prepare_release>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:9
msgid "Facility preparation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:11
msgid ""
"Before beginning to make a release, use the ``*_requirements.txt`` files to "
"ensure that you have the needed software. Most software can be installed "
"with pip, but some will require apt-get, dnf, or whatever your system uses "
"for software. You will also need a GitHub personal access token (PAT) to "
"push the documentation. There are a few ways to streamline things:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:17
msgid ""
"Git can be set up to use a keyring to store your GitHub personal access "
"token. Search online for the details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:19
msgid ""
"You can use the ``keyring`` app to store the PyPI password for twine. See "
"the online twine documentation for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:24
msgid "Release preparation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:27
msgid "Add/drop Python versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:29
msgid "When adding or dropping Python versions, three files need to be edited:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:31
msgid ".github/workflows/wheels.yml  # for github cibuildwheel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:32
msgid ".travis.yml  # for cibuildwheel aarch64 builds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:33
msgid "setup.py  # for classifier and minimum version check."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:35
msgid ""
"Make these changes in an ordinary PR against main and backport if necessary. "
"Using the `BLD:` prefix (build label) for the commit summary will cause the "
"wheel builds to be run so that the changes will be tested, We currently "
"release wheels for new Python versions after the first Python rc once "
"manylinux and cibuildwheel support it. For Python 3.11 we were able to "
"release within a week of the rc1 announcement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:43
msgid "Backport Pull Requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:45
msgid ""
"Changes that have been marked for this release must be backported to the "
"maintenance/1.21.x branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:49
msgid "Update release documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:51
msgid ""
"Four documents usually need to be updated or created before making a release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:53
msgid "The changelog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:54
msgid "The release-notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:55
msgid "The ``.mailmap`` file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:56
msgid "The ``doc/source/release.rst`` file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:58
msgid ""
"These changes should be made as an ordinary PR against the maintenance "
"branch. After release all files except ``doc/source/release.rst``  will need "
"to be forward ported to the main branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:63
msgid "Generate the changelog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:65
msgid "The changelog is generated using the changelog tool::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:67
msgid ""
"$ python tools/changelog.py $GITHUB v1.20.0..maintenance/1.21.x > doc/"
"changelog/1.21.0-changelog.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:69
msgid ""
"where ``GITHUB`` contains your GitHub access token. The text will need to be "
"checked for non-standard contributor names and dependabot entries removed. "
"It is also a good idea to remove any links that may be present in the PR "
"titles as they don't translate well to markdown, replace them with "
"monospaced text. The non-standard contributor names should be fixed by "
"updating the ``.mailmap`` file, which is a lot of work. It is best to make "
"several trial runs before reaching this point and ping the malefactors using "
"a GitHub issue to get the needed information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:79
msgid "Finish the release notes"
msgstr "完成發行備註"

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:81
msgid ""
"If this is the first release in a series the release note is generated, see "
"the release note in ``doc/release/upcoming_changes/README.rst`` to see how "
"to do this. Generating the release notes will also delete all the news "
"fragment files in ``doc/release/upcoming_changes/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:86
msgid ""
"The generated release note will always need some fixups, the introduction "
"will need to be written, and significant changes should be called out. For "
"patch releases the changelog text may also be appended, but not for the "
"initial release as it is too long. Check previous release notes to see how "
"this is done. Note that the ``:orphan:`` markup at the top, if present, will "
"need changing to ``.. currentmodule:: numpy`` and the ``doc/source/release."
"rst`` index file will need updating."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:95
msgid "Check the ``pavement.py`` file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:97
msgid ""
"Check that the pavement.py file points to the correct release notes. It "
"should have been updated after the last release, but if not, fix it now::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:100
msgid "$ gvim pavement.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:104
msgid "Release walkthrough"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:106
msgid ""
"Note that in the code snippets below, ``upstream`` refers to the root "
"repository on GitHub and ``origin`` to its fork in your personal GitHub "
"repositories. You may need to make adjustments if you have not forked the "
"repository but simply cloned it locally. You can also edit ``.git/config`` "
"and add ``upstream`` if it isn't already present."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:113
msgid "1. Prepare the release commit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:115
msgid ""
"Checkout the branch for the release, make sure it is up to date, and clean "
"the repository::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:118
msgid ""
"$ git checkout maintenance/1.21.x\n"
"$ git pull upstream maintenance/1.21.x\n"
"$ git submodule update\n"
"$ git clean -xdfq"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:123
msgid "Sanity check::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:125
msgid "$ python3 -m spin test -m full"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:127
msgid ""
"Tag the release and push the tag. This requires write permission for the "
"numpy repository::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:130
msgid ""
"$ git tag -a -s v1.21.0 -m\"NumPy 1.21.0 release\"\n"
"$ git push upstream v1.21.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:133
msgid "If you need to delete the tag due to error::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:135
msgid ""
"$ git tag -d v1.21.0\n"
"$ git push --delete upstream v1.21.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:139
msgid "2. Build wheels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:142
msgid "Build wheels via cibuildwheel (preferred)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:144
msgid ""
"Tagging the build at the beginning of this process will trigger a wheel "
"build via cibuildwheel and upload wheels and an sdist to the staging repo. "
"The CI run on github actions (for all x86-based and macOS arm64 wheels) "
"takes about 1 1/4 hours. The CI run on travis (for aarch64) takes less time. "
"You can check for uploaded files at the `staging repository`_, but note that "
"it is not closely synched with what you see of the running jobs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:151
msgid "If you wish to manually trigger a wheel build, you can do so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:153
msgid ""
"On github actions -> `Wheel builder`_ there is a \"Run workflow\" button, "
"click on it and choose the tag to build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:155
msgid ""
"On travis_ there is a \"More Options\" button, click on it and choose a "
"branch to build. There does not appear to be an option to build a tag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:158
msgid ""
"If a wheel build fails for unrelated reasons, you can rerun it individually:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:160
msgid ""
"On github actions select `Wheel builder`_ click on the commit that contains "
"the build you want to rerun. On the left there is a list of wheel builds, "
"select the one you want to rerun and on the resulting page hit the "
"counterclockwise arrows button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:164
msgid ""
"On travis_ select the failing build, which will take you to the travis job "
"for that build. Hit the restart job button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:167
msgid ""
"Note that if you do need to rerun jobs, you will need to delete the uploaded "
"file, if any, in the anaconda `staging repository`_, The old files will not "
"be overwritten."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:177
msgid "3. Download wheels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:179
msgid ""
"When the wheels have all been successfully built and staged, download them "
"from the Anaconda staging directory using the ``tools/download-wheels.py`` "
"script::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:182
msgid ""
"$ cd ../numpy\n"
"$ mkdir -p release/installers\n"
"$ python3 tools/download-wheels.py 1.21.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:188
msgid "4. Generate the README files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:190
msgid ""
"This needs to be done after all installers are downloaded, but before the "
"pavement file is updated for continued development::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:193
msgid "$ paver write_release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:197
msgid ""
"5. Reset the maintenance branch into a development state (skip for "
"prereleases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:199
msgid ""
"Create release notes for next release and edit them to set the version. "
"These notes will be a skeleton and have little content::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:202
msgid ""
"$ cp doc/source/release/template.rst doc/source/release/1.21.1-notes.rst\n"
"$ gvim doc/source/release/1.21.1-notes.rst\n"
"$ git add doc/source/release/1.21.1-notes.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:206
msgid ""
"Add new release notes to the documentation release list and update the "
"``RELEASE_NOTES`` variable in ``pavement.py``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:209
msgid "$ gvim doc/source/release.rst pavement.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:211
msgid "Commit the result::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:213
msgid ""
"$ git commit -a -m\"REL: prepare 1.21.x for further development\"\n"
"$ git push upstream HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:218
msgid "6. Upload to PyPI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:220
msgid ""
"Upload to PyPI using ``twine``. A recent version of ``twine`` of is needed "
"after recent PyPI changes, version ``3.4.1`` was used here::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:223
msgid ""
"$ cd ../numpy\n"
"$ twine upload release/installers/*.whl\n"
"$ twine upload release/installers/numpy-1.21.0.tar.gz  # Upload last."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:227
msgid ""
"If one of the commands breaks in the middle, you may need to selectively "
"upload the remaining files because PyPI does not allow the same file to be "
"uploaded twice. The source file should be uploaded last to avoid "
"synchronization problems that might occur if pip users access the files "
"while this is in process, causing pip to build from source rather than "
"downloading a binary wheel. PyPI only allows a single source distribution, "
"here we have chosen the zip archive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:237
msgid "7. Upload files to github"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:239
msgid ""
"Go to `<https://github.com/numpy/numpy/releases>`_, there should be a "
"``v1.21.0 tag``, click on it and hit the edit button for that tag. There are "
"two ways to add files, using an editable text window and as binary uploads. "
"Start by editing the ``release/README.md`` that is translated from the rst "
"version using pandoc. Things that will need fixing: PR lines from the "
"changelog, if included, are wrapped and need unwrapping, links should be "
"changed to monospaced text. Then copy the contents to the clipboard and "
"paste them into the text window. It may take several tries to get it look "
"right. Then"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:248
msgid "Upload ``release/installers/numpy-1.21.0.tar.gz`` as a binary file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:249
msgid "Upload ``release/README.rst`` as a binary file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:250
msgid "Upload ``doc/changelog/1.21.0-changelog.rst`` as a binary file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:251
msgid "Check the pre-release button if this is a pre-releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:252
msgid "Hit the ``{Publish,Update} release`` button at the bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:256
msgid "8. Upload documents to numpy.org (skip for prereleases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:258
msgid "You will need a GitHub personal access token to push the update."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:260
msgid ""
"This step is only needed for final releases and can be skipped for pre-"
"releases and most patch releases. ``make merge-doc`` clones the ``numpy/"
"doc`` repo into ``doc/build/merge`` and updates it with the new "
"documentation::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:264
msgid ""
"$ git clean -xdfq\n"
"$ git co v1.21.0\n"
"$ pushd doc\n"
"$ make docenv && source docenv/bin/activate\n"
"$ make merge-doc\n"
"$ pushd build/merge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:271
msgid ""
"If the release series is a new one, you will need to add a new section to "
"the ``doc/build/merge/index.html`` front page just after the \"insert here\" "
"comment::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:274
msgid "$ gvim index.html +/'insert here'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:276
msgid ""
"Further, update the version-switcher json file to add the new release and "
"update the version marked `(stable)`::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:279
msgid "$ gvim _static/versions.json"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:281
msgid ""
"Otherwise, only the ``zip`` link should be updated with the new tag name. "
"Since we are no longer generating ``pdf`` files, remove the line for the "
"``pdf`` files if present::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:285
msgid "$ gvim index.html +/'tag v1.21'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:287
msgid ""
"You can \"test run\" the new documentation in a browser to make sure the "
"links work::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:290
msgid "$ firefox index.html  # or google-chrome, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:292
msgid "Update the stable link and update::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:294
msgid ""
"$ ln -sfn 1.21 stable\n"
"$ ls -l  # check the link"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:297
msgid ""
"Once everything seems satisfactory, update, commit and upload the changes::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:299
msgid ""
"$ python3 update.py\n"
"$ git commit -a -m\"Add documentation for v1.21.0\"\n"
"$ git push\n"
"$ deactivate\n"
"$ popd\n"
"$ popd"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:308
msgid "9. Announce the release on numpy.org (skip for prereleases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:310
msgid ""
"This assumes that you have forked `<https://github.com/numpy/numpy.org>`_::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:312
msgid ""
"$ cd ../numpy.org\n"
"$ git checkout main\n"
"$ git pull upstream main\n"
"$ git checkout -b announce-numpy-1.21.0\n"
"$ gvim content/en/news.md"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:318
msgid ""
"For all releases, go to the bottom of the page and add a one line link. Look "
"to the previous links for example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:320
msgid ""
"For the ``*.0`` release in a cycle, add a new section at the top with a "
"short description of the new features and point the news link to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:323
msgid "commit and push::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:325
msgid ""
"$ git commit -a -m\"announce the NumPy 1.21.0 release\"\n"
"$ git push origin HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:328
msgid "Go to your Github fork and make a pull request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:331
msgid "10. Announce to mailing lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:333
msgid ""
"The release should be announced on the numpy-discussion, scipy-devel, scipy-"
"user, and python-announce-list mailing lists. Look at previous announcements "
"for the basic template. The contributor and PR lists are the same as "
"generated for the release notes above. If you crosspost, make sure that "
"python-announce-list is BCC so that replies will not be sent to that list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:341
msgid "11. Post-release tasks (skip for prereleases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:343
msgid "Checkout main and forward port the documentation changes::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:345
msgid ""
"$ git checkout -b post-1.21.0-release-update\n"
"$ git checkout maintenance/1.21.x doc/source/release/1.21.0-notes.rst\n"
"$ git checkout maintenance/1.21.x doc/changelog/1.21.0-changelog.rst\n"
"$ git checkout maintenance/1.21.x .mailmap  # only if updated for release.\n"
"$ gvim doc/source/release.rst  # Add link to new notes\n"
"$ git status  # check status before commit\n"
"$ git commit -a -m\"MAINT: Update main after 1.21.0 release.\"\n"
"$ git push origin HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:354
msgid "Go to GitHub and make a PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:357
msgid "12. Update oldest-supported-numpy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:359
msgid ""
"If this release is the first one to support a new Python version, or the "
"first to provide wheels for a new platform or PyPy version, the version "
"pinnings in https://github.com/scipy/oldest-supported-numpy should be "
"updated. Either submit a PR with changes to ``setup.cfg`` there, or open an "
"issue with info on needed changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/releasing.rst:26
msgid "Branch walkthrough"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:1
msgid ""
"This guide contains a walkthrough of branching NumPy 1.21.x on Linux.  The "
"commands can be copied into the command line, but be sure to replace 1.21 "
"and 1.22 by the correct versions. It is good practice to make ``.mailmap`` "
"as current as possible before making the branch, that may take several weeks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:6
msgid ""
"This should be read together with the :ref:`general release guide "
"<prepare_release>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:10
msgid "Branching"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:13
msgid "Make the branch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:15
msgid ""
"This is only needed when starting a new maintenance branch. Because NumPy "
"now depends on tags to determine the version, the start of a new development "
"cycle in the main branch needs an annotated tag. That is done as follows::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:20
msgid ""
"$ git checkout main\n"
"$ git pull upstream main\n"
"$ git commit --allow-empty -m'REL: Begin NumPy 1.22.0 development'\n"
"$ git push upstream HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:25
msgid "If the push fails because new PRs have been merged, do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:27
msgid "$ git pull --rebase upstream"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:29
msgid "and repeat the push. Once the push succeeds, tag it::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:31
msgid ""
"$ git tag -a -s v1.22.0.dev0 -m'Begin NumPy 1.22.0 development'\n"
"$ git push upstream v1.22.0.dev0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:34
msgid "then make the new branch and push it::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:36
msgid ""
"$ git branch maintenance/1.21.x HEAD^\n"
"$ git push upstream maintenance/1.21.x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:40
msgid "Prepare the main branch for further development"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:42
msgid "Make a PR branch to prepare main for further development::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:44
msgid "$ git checkout -b 'prepare-main-for-1.22.0-development' v1.22.0.dev0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:46
msgid "Delete the release note fragments::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:48
msgid "$ git rm doc/release/upcoming_changes/[0-9]*.*.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:50
msgid "Create the new release notes skeleton and add to index::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:52
msgid ""
"$ cp doc/source/release/template.rst doc/source/release/1.22.0-notes.rst\n"
"$ gvim doc/source/release/1.22.0-notes.rst  # put the correct version\n"
"$ git add doc/source/release/1.22.0-notes.rst\n"
"$ gvim doc/source/release.rst  # add new notes to notes index\n"
"$ git add doc/source/release.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:58
msgid ""
"Update ``pavement.py`` and update the ``RELEASE_NOTES`` variable to point to "
"the new notes::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:61
msgid ""
"$ gvim pavement.py\n"
"$ git add pavement.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:64
msgid ""
"Update ``cversions.txt`` to add current release. There should be no new hash "
"to worry about at this early point, just add a comment following previous "
"practice::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:68
msgid ""
"$ gvim numpy/core/code_generators/cversions.txt\n"
"$ git add numpy/core/code_generators/cversions.txt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:71
msgid "Check your work, commit it, and push::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:73
msgid ""
"$ git status  # check work\n"
"$ git commit -m'REL: Prepare main for NumPy 1.22.0 development'\n"
"$ git push origin HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:77
msgid "Now make a pull request."
msgstr ""
